                                        <br />
                                        <br />
                                        <span class="fw-bold">Charity -</span> The new platform can serve as complementary with their already existing platforms, such as social media, intending to fill in the gaps that social media has left unresolved in resolving barriers in giving. One of the key issues the pandemic has brought to charitable institutions is a significant drop in funding that threatens to affect programs and services supporting vulnerable people in our society. CharitAble intends to ease the barriers in giving, potentially inspire and retain more donors thus a more likely of receiving higher funding from donations, as well as increasing productivity and interaction from inspired volunteers. The platform also intends to promote a level of greater transparency among the charity and donor in metrics such as capacity, timeline and funds, thus developing more healthy expectations for all parties.

                                        <br />
                                        <br />
                                        <span class="fw-bold">Volunteers -</span> The result of the study would help them in searching for organizations that they would like to volunteer with. They can check out the page profile of the charity, taking in mind the charitable institution's mission and vision if it aligns with them. The proposed platform also provides a job-search like feature wherein charities could post volunteer posting, noting the required skills, traits, moreover if the volunteering work is remote and is open for volunteers without any prior experience. This feature is useful as volunteers highlighted issues such as the lack of awareness on the available volunteering opportunities and hesitancy from information barriers if charities accept volunteers without any prior experience and skills.
                                        <br />
                                        <br />
