                                        In order for charities to solicit donations through our platform, they must apply for a verification status by submitting required documents. The two primary required documents are SEC Articles of Incorporation, to determine if an organization is registered  as a legal non profit organization entity. This particular document could be validated using the SEC Express System to determine its authenticity. Another document required by our platform is the DSWD Solicitation Permit, this document provides non-profit organizations legality to solicit donations for its programs. Every  application  for a solicitation permit requires thorough checking of the organization program planning and management, manually by the admins of CharitAble,. Both  of these documents ensure that the donors are donating their hard earned money to legitimate organizations with efficient financial management and detailed planning while minimizing the risk of any fraud or scams. Unverified charities could still use all the features and functionalities of the platform with the exception of donation solicitation.
